derstanding the role that the Lin Lan stories played in modern China. Appendixes include information on tale types and biographies of the writers and contributors.A reflection of Chinese culture, history, and values, The Dragon Daughter and Other Lin Lan Fairy Tales is a captivating testament to the power of storytelling.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChildren's stories, Chinesey20th century. 0aFairy taleszChinay20th century. 0aFolklorezChinay20th century. 0aHumorous stories, Chinesey20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aA Book Of.  aAdvertising.  aAmerican Council of Learned Societies.  aAndrei Codrescu.  aBerthold Auerbach.  aBook.  aBrothers Grimm.  aCat and Dog.  aCat.  aCinnabar.  aCity God (China).  aCoffin.  aConcerned.  aConfucianism.  aCover Her Face.  aDeep sea.  aDelicacy.  aDie Gartenlaube.  aDragon robe.  aDuan Chengshi.  aEast Room.  aFiction.  aFolk and Fairy Tales.  aFranco-Prussian War.  aFrederick the Great.  aGenre.  aGerman literature.  aGhost marriage (Chinese).  aHandkerchief.  aHermann Hesse.  aHistorical fiction.  aImperial examination.  aInterior design.  aInto the West (miniseries).  aJack Zipes.  aJean Paul.  aJiangsu.  aJujube.  aKurt Schwitters.  aLeash.  aLoquat.  aLove at first sight.  aLu Xun (Three Kingdoms).  aLu Xun.  aMaria Tatar.  aMarina Warner.  aMarry You.  aMass murder.  aMeal.  aMillet.  aModernism.  aMother Courage.  aNaomi Mitchison.  aNarrative.  aNew Culture Movement.  aNovel.  aNovelist.  aNovella.  aOld Book (ghost).  aOliver Goldsmith.  aOral tradition.  aOscar Wilde.  aPen name.  aPhilip Pullman.  aPhilistinism.  aPlough.  aPoetry.  aPorcelain.  aPorridge.  aProse.  aPublication.  aPublishing. 